race.comment: ROSE OF SHIRAZ (9) resumes here but has revved up for this with a recent trial placing and has won twice when fresh before. She'll handle the soft conditions and it wouldn't surprise to see her come out on top on resumption. THE HAMO (7) is some niggle on the Soft track, though his latest performance at Gatton says he's up to winning a race like this. Steps out slightly to 1200m now and can be in this race for a very long way. JOY A PLENTY (5) has impressed since returning, winning at this track and trip last time out. Soft track is the query, though if she can run up to her last start figures then she'll be right in the mix again. BIG BOY GEORGE (2) comes here third-up into the campaign and steps back out to 1200m. Looks to get conditions to suit here so a better run is on the cards.
